00:08:33,805 --> 00:08:35,849
OH, IS THAT HOW
YOU WERE BORN?

240
00:08:35,933 --> 00:08:37,434
HOW WERE YOU BORN?
SHORT?

241
00:08:37,518 --> 00:08:38,727
MMM, IT'S LIKE THAT.

242
00:08:38,810 --> 00:08:40,270
YOU WANT ME TO TAKE
THE GLOVES OFF?

243
00:08:40,354 --> 00:08:41,980
GO AHEAD, DAVE!
SHOW ME WHAT YOU'RE PACKING.

244
00:08:42,064 --> 00:08:42,981
(DAVE BARKS)

245
00:08:43,065 --> 00:08:44,191
DAVE:
THAT'S MY ATTACK DOG.

246
00:08:44,274 --> 00:08:45,776
I TRAINED HIM
TO CRAVE WEAKLING.

247
00:08:45,859 --> 00:08:47,528
ADAM:
YO, I WILL DOG WHISPER
YOUR BUTT.

248
00:08:47,611 --> 00:08:48,612
I WILL OWN YOU!

249
00:08:48,695 --> 00:08:50,364
DAVE:
YOU CAN'T OWN ME, HOLMES,
I GOT THE MIND OF A NINJA,

250
00:08:50,447 --> 00:08:52,950
THE EYE OF THE TIGER,
THE COURAGE OF A LION!

251
00:08:53,033 --> 00:08:56,203
ADAM:
THE BRAIN OF A SCARECROW,
AND THE HEART OF A TIN MAN.

252
00:08:56,286 --> 00:08:57,204
BOOM!

253
00:08:57,287 --> 00:08:58,330
DAVE:
OH, YOU DID NOT
JUST "BOOM" ME!

254
00:08:58,413 --> 00:08:59,498
ADAM:
OH, I BOOMED YOU, DOROTHY.

255
00:08:59,581 --> 00:09:01,625
I BOOMED YOU BIG TIME,
AND I'LL DO IT AGAIN!

256
00:09:01,708 --> 00:09:03,627
DAVE: OH NO, YOU-
ADAM: BOOM!

257
00:09:03,710 --> 00:09:05,045
(LAUGHS) ALL RIGHT,
WELL, LOOK,

258
00:09:05,128 --> 00:09:07,714
WE'LL SEE HOW FUNNY YOU ARE
WHEN WE'RE ON THE AIR.

259
00:09:07,798 --> 00:09:09,299
ARE WE READY?
LET'S DO THIS.

260
00:09:09,383 --> 00:09:10,592
(MUFFLED LAUGHTER
FROM OUTSIDE BOOTH)

261
00:09:10,676 --> 00:09:12,302
IT'S BEING DONE,
MY FRIEND.

262
00:09:12,386 --> 00:09:13,887
(STUDENTS LAUGH AND CLAP)

263
00:09:13,971 --> 00:09:14,888
WE'RE ON AIR?

264
00:09:14,972 --> 00:09:16,890
AND THE PEOPLE HAVE SPOKEN.

265
00:09:16,974 --> 00:09:18,976
(CHEERING AND CLAPPING)

266
00:09:21,562 --> 00:09:22,563
BOOM!

267
00:09:24,273 --> 00:09:25,274
(SIGHS)

268
00:09:26,942 --> 00:09:29,069
ADAM:
"MANO A MANO"
WITH DAVE AND ADAM!

269
00:09:29,152 --> 00:09:30,654
THIS IS GONNA BE AWESOME!

270
00:09:30,737 --> 00:09:31,822
DAVE:
LOOK, I GOTTA SAY
I WANTED TO BEAT YOU,

271
00:09:31,905 --> 00:09:34,283
BUT IT'LL BE WAY MORE FUN
TO JOIN YOU.

272
00:09:34,366 --> 00:09:35,367
WE RULE!

273
00:09:39,913 --> 00:09:42,207
I'LL BE OUT IN A SEC.

274
00:09:50,924 --> 00:09:51,925
(DOOR CLICKS)

275
00:09:53,510 --> 00:09:55,012
AH, YOU...CAME IN.

276
00:09:56,138 --> 00:09:57,472
YOU GOTTA WHIZ TOO?

277
00:09:57,556 --> 00:10:00,559
NO, JUST, UH...
WANNA WASH MY HANDS.

278
00:10:01,977 --> 00:10:04,730
SO, WHAT ARE WE GOING
TO TALK ABOUT TOMORROW?

279
00:10:04,813 --> 00:10:06,440
DAVE:
UH...GIRLS? MUSIC?

280
00:10:07,441 --> 00:10:09,359
WHATEVER WE WANT.

281
00:10:10,777 --> 00:10:13,363
DAVE:
OR WE COULD, UH,
PUSH THE ENVELOPE,

282
00:10:13,447 --> 00:10:15,157
TAKE ON SOME ISSUES,

283
00:10:15,240 --> 00:10:17,743
SEE HOW FAR WE CAN GO
UNTIL SIMPSON REAMS OUT SAV.

284
00:10:21,246 --> 00:10:22,831
ADAM?

285
00:10:23,832 --> 00:10:25,292
WHAT? OH! UM...

286
00:10:25,375 --> 00:10:26,710
YEAH, SIMPSON.

287
00:10:26,793 --> 00:10:27,878
DUDE,
YOU'VE GOT ISSUES!

288
00:10:27,961 --> 00:10:29,546
NO, DAVE,
I WASN'T STARING!

289
00:10:29,630 --> 00:10:32,257
LOOK, WHATEVER.
I'VE GOT CLASS.

290
00:10:45,437 --> 00:10:47,564
DAVE:
EL PRESIDENTE,
YOU GOT A MINUTE?

291
00:10:47,648 --> 00:10:51,026
DAVE! YEAH.
ANYTHING FOR MY NEW SHOCK JOCK!

292
00:10:51,109 --> 00:10:52,027
WHERE'S YOUR OTHER HALF?

293
00:10:52,110 --> 00:10:53,028
DAVE:
YOU MEAN ADAM?

294
00:10:53,111 --> 00:10:54,988
SAV:
YEAH. YOU TWO ARE ALL THE BUZZ.

295
00:10:55,072 --> 00:10:56,865
DUDE,
CHECK THIS OUT.

296
00:10:56,949 --> 00:10:58,492
NEW T-SHIRT PROTOTYPE.

297
00:10:58,575 --> 00:11:00,369
MADE IT MYSELF.

298
00:11:00,452 --> 00:11:02,788
YEAH, LOOK,
IT-IT'S GREAT AND...

299
00:11:02,871 --> 00:11:04,665
I HAD FUN AND EVERYTHING,
BUT...

300
00:11:04,748 --> 00:11:06,083
I GOTTA QUIT THE SHOW.

301
00:11:06,166 --> 00:11:08,752
UM, YOU HAVEN'T EVEN
STARTED YET.

302
00:11:08,836 --> 00:11:10,212
AND WHY?

303
00:11:10,295 --> 00:11:11,880
I CAN'T REALLY TALK
ABOUT IT.

304
00:11:11,964 --> 00:11:12,881
LOOK, ME AND ADAM,

305
00:11:12,965 --> 00:11:14,299
WE'RE JUST,
WE'RE NOT A GOOD FIT.

306
00:11:14,383 --> 00:11:16,593
IT'S JUST A RADIO SHOW,
DUDE!

307
00:11:16,677 --> 00:11:18,011
YOU'RE NOT MARRYING ANYONE.

308
00:11:18,095 --> 00:11:19,847
BESIDES, PEOPLE LOVE
YOU TWO TOGETHER!

309
00:11:19,930 --> 00:11:23,475
YOUR FIRST BROADCAST
GOT A HUNDRED EMAILS.

310
00:11:23,559 --> 00:11:25,394
A HUNDRED?!

311
00:11:25,477 --> 00:11:26,603
I'M SAYING,
GIVE IT A WEEK,

312
00:11:26,687 --> 00:11:28,689
YOU TWO ARE GONNA BE
THE MOST POPULAR GUYS

313
00:11:28,772 --> 00:11:29,690
AT THIS SCHOOL.

314
00:11:29,773 --> 00:11:31,650
YOU WANNA GIVE THAT UP?

315
00:11:32,651 --> 00:11:35,863
OFFICER TURNER:
SON! YOUR SHOW WAS HILARIOUS!

316
00:11:35,946 --> 00:11:37,322
YEAH? YOU HEARD?

317
00:11:37,406 --> 00:11:38,365
YOU DA MAN!

318
00:11:38,448 --> 00:11:40,242
YOU'RE GONNA BE BACK ON
AGAIN TOMORROW, RIGHT?

319
00:11:43,120 --> 00:11:44,288
YEAH, YEAH.

320
00:11:44,371 --> 00:11:45,455
CAN'T WAIT TO HEAR IT.

321
00:11:45,539 --> 00:11:46,540
PROUD OF YOU.

322
00:11:50,919 --> 00:11:52,087
TWELVE NOON.

323
00:11:53,088 --> 00:11:56,675
♪ "MANO A MANO"
WITH DAVE AND ADAM! ♪

324
00:11:59,344 --> 00:12:00,262
(SIGHS)

325
00:12:00,345 --> 00:12:01,889
CHARLIE:
HOME SAFE AND SOUND.

326
00:12:01,972 --> 00:12:04,308
SO YOUR FRIEND ELISE
WAS SO NICE TO ME!

327
00:12:04,391 --> 00:12:06,393
DOESN'T EVERYONE LOVE YOU
AT FIRST SIGHT?

328
00:12:06,476 --> 00:12:07,477
I WISH!

329
00:12:08,520 --> 00:12:11,106
I'M NOT EXACTLY FITTING IN
AT SCHOOL.

330
00:12:11,190 --> 00:12:13,066
IT'S HIGH SCHOOL;
WHO DOES?

331
00:12:13,150 --> 00:12:14,860
PLUS, YOU ONLY HAVE
A FEW MONTHS LEFT.

332
00:12:14,943 --> 00:12:16,361
NEGATIVE.

333
00:12:16,445 --> 00:12:17,988
IT'S A LONG,
BORING STORY,

334
00:12:18,071 --> 00:12:20,616
BUT I'M SHORT
A FEW CREDITS,

335
00:12:20,699 --> 00:12:21,867
SO I'LL BE BACK
NEXT YEAR,

336
00:12:21,950 --> 00:12:23,619
AND THE FEW FRIENDS
THAT I DO HAVE

337
00:12:23,702 --> 00:12:25,746
WILL BE HEADING
TO THEIR IVORY TOWERS.

338
00:12:25,829 --> 00:12:26,830
I'LL BE ALL ALONE.

339
00:12:26,914 --> 00:12:29,124
HEY, YOU'LL HAVE ME.

340
00:12:29,208 --> 00:12:30,501
(LAUGHS)

341
00:12:30,584 --> 00:12:32,544
I SHOULD REALLY GO,

342
00:12:32,628 --> 00:12:33,921
BEFORE MY BOSS NOTICES
I'VE BEEN GONE

343
00:12:34,004 --> 00:12:35,964
FOR AN HOUR AND A HALF!

344
00:12:36,048 --> 00:12:37,007
ARE YOU SURE
YOU DON'T WANT ME

345
00:12:37,090 --> 00:12:38,509
TO DROP YOU OFF AT SCHOOL?

346
00:12:38,592 --> 00:12:40,260
VERY SURE.

347
00:12:40,344 --> 00:12:42,804
WHAT ABOUT TONIGHT?
ANY PLANS?

348
00:12:42,888 --> 00:12:45,057
YEAH.
BOWLING NIGHT.

349
00:12:45,599 --> 00:12:46,517
OH.

350
00:12:46,600 --> 00:12:49,144
THERE'S ALWAYS ROOM
FOR ONE MORE.

351
00:12:49,228 --> 00:12:51,396
REALLY?
I LOVE BOWLING.

352
00:12:52,397 --> 00:12:54,066
I MEAN,
I ASSUME I WILL.

353
00:12:54,149 --> 00:12:56,068
YOU'VE NEVER BEEN?

354
00:12:56,151 --> 00:12:58,820
WELL THEN,
TONIGHT'S YOUR LUCKY NIGHT!

355
00:12:58,904 --> 00:12:59,905
(GIGGLES)

356
00:13:01,615 --> 00:13:03,325
FIONA, WHAT ARE YOU
DOING HERE?

357
00:13:03,408 --> 00:13:05,577
MOM, I THOUGHT YOU HAD
A SPA THING.

358
00:13:05,661 --> 00:13:06,954
LARA:
I CANCELLED.

359
00:13:07,037 --> 00:13:08,664
WHY AREN'T YOU AT SCHOOL?

360
00:13:09,665 --> 00:13:10,707
I SHOULD GO.

361
00:13:10,791 --> 00:13:11,708
LARA:
THAT'S AN EXCELLENT IDEA.

362
00:13:11,792 --> 00:13:14,378
MY DAUGHTER AND I NEED TO TALK.

363
00:13:22,719 --> 00:13:39,403
♪♪♪

364
00:13:40,404 --> 00:13:41,321
HI, KATIE.

365
00:13:41,405 --> 00:13:42,406
CLARE, WHAT DO YOU
HAVE FOR ME?

366
00:13:42,489 --> 00:13:43,490
ONE SAMPLE ARTICLE,

367
00:13:43,574 --> 00:13:44,867
SIGNED, SEALED,
AND DELIVERED.

368
00:13:44,950 --> 00:13:47,619
W-WELL, NOT SEALED,
BUT THE OTHER TWO.

369
00:13:47,703 --> 00:13:49,329
GREAT.
UH, LEAVE IT ON MY DESK.

370
00:13:49,413 --> 00:13:50,747
(SIGHS NERVOUSLY)

371
00:13:54,751 --> 00:13:56,170
SO WHEN DO YOU THINK
YOU'LL GET A CHANCE

372
00:13:56,253 --> 00:13:57,671
TO READ MY ARTICLE?

373
00:13:57,754 --> 00:13:59,590
KATIE:
I HAVE SOME TIME NEXT FRIDAY.

374
00:13:59,673 --> 00:14:00,757
NEXT FRIDAY?!

375
00:14:00,841 --> 00:14:01,884
I'M JOKING, CLARE.

376
00:14:01,967 --> 00:14:03,010
UNCLENCH!

377
00:14:03,093 --> 00:14:05,721
PEOPLE SAY I'M INTENSE.

378
00:14:05,804 --> 00:14:06,763
HOW ABOUT I READ IT NOW?

379
00:14:06,847 --> 00:14:07,848
GREAT!

380
00:14:13,770 --> 00:14:16,148
I SAID A HUNDRED WORDS.

381
00:14:16,231 --> 00:14:17,941
I WANTED TO DO MORE
THAN A FLUFF PIECE.

382
00:14:18,025 --> 00:14:19,234
THIS IS FIVE PAGES!

383
00:14:19,318 --> 00:14:21,904
YOU PUT IN FOOTNOTES,
AND THERE'S AN APPENDIX!

384
00:14:21,987 --> 00:14:23,447
KIDS AREN'T GOING
TO READ THIS.

385
00:14:23,530 --> 00:14:25,365
WELL,
YOU DON'T KNOW THAT.

386
00:14:25,449 --> 00:14:28,577
YOU'RE TELLING ME
WHAT I DON'T KNOW?

387
00:14:28,660 --> 00:14:32,122
MAYBE IT JUST NEEDS
A CATCHY HEADLINE.

388
00:14:32,206 --> 00:14:35,083
I'M SORRY, CLARE,
THE NEWSPAPER STAFF IS FULL.

389
00:14:40,297 --> 00:14:42,299
(CELL PHONE BEEPS)

390
00:14:43,467 --> 00:14:45,636
I GUESS DAVE
ISN'T COMING.

391
00:14:45,719 --> 00:14:47,262
I ONLY WENT INTO
THE GUY'S BATHROOM

392
00:14:47,346 --> 00:14:49,556
BECAUSE I WANTED HIM
TO SEE ME AS A GUY.

393
00:14:49,640 --> 00:14:51,308
BACKFIRE MUCH?

394
00:14:51,391 --> 00:14:52,976
BECAUSE YOU GOT CAUGHT
SNEAKING A PEEK.

395
00:14:53,060 --> 00:14:56,897
NO! I-I TOLD YOU,
I WASN'T SNEAKING A PEEK!

396
00:14:56,980 --> 00:14:59,650
I JUST WANTED TO CHECK OUT
HIS STANCE AT THE URINAL.

397
00:14:59,733 --> 00:15:01,360
WHY THE SUDDEN INTEREST
IN URINALS?

398
00:15:04,404 --> 00:15:06,156
BECAUSE OF THIS.

399
00:15:07,157 --> 00:15:08,700
WHAT THE HECK IS THAT?!

400
00:15:08,784 --> 00:15:10,369
ADAM:
A STAND-TO-PEE DEVICE.

401
00:15:10,452 --> 00:15:12,162
I GOT IT ONLINE.

402
00:15:12,246 --> 00:15:14,498
IT'S SO I CAN-
STAND TO PEE?

403
00:15:15,499 --> 00:15:16,917
HOW DOES IT WORK?

404
00:15:17,000 --> 00:15:19,586
HOW DO YOU THINK
IT WORKS?

405
00:15:20,587 --> 00:15:22,923
ELI:
MAYDAY, TEN O'CLOCK.

406
00:15:23,006 --> 00:15:23,924
WHAT DO I SAY?

407
00:15:24,007 --> 00:15:26,385
JUST BE COOL.
ACT LIKE IT NEVER HAPPEND.

408
00:15:26,468 --> 00:15:27,928
NO, BUT IF-IF DAVE
CAN'T HANDLE THIS,

409
00:15:28,011 --> 00:15:29,179
THEN WHO CAN?

410
00:15:30,180 --> 00:15:31,181
GIVE HIM SOME CREDIT.

411
00:15:33,267 --> 00:15:34,434
HEY.

412
00:15:34,518 --> 00:15:36,603
HEY, I THOUGHT
YOU WEREN'T COMING.

413
00:15:36,687 --> 00:15:40,399
WELL, UH, WE HAVE A SHOW
TO PLAN FOR, DON'T WE?

414
00:15:40,482 --> 00:15:41,817
WELL, GOOD LUCK.

415
00:15:43,652 --> 00:15:46,029
WELL, WE SHOULD GET STARTED.

416
00:15:46,113 --> 00:15:47,114
UH...

417
00:15:52,286 --> 00:15:54,288
MOM, WILL YOU LET ME
EXPLAIN?

418
00:15:54,371 --> 00:15:56,540
WHY YOU SKIPPED SCHOOL?

419
00:15:56,623 --> 00:15:58,208
IT WAS A REALLY HARD DAY
FOR ME.

420
00:15:58,292 --> 00:15:59,793
SO YOU DECIDED TO LEAVE.

421
00:15:59,877 --> 00:16:00,794
AND YOU DECIDED
TO EMBARRASS ME

422
00:16:00,878 --> 00:16:02,588
IN FRONT OF CHARLIE!

423
00:16:02,671 --> 00:16:04,464
THAT IS NOT WHAT
WE'RE DISCUSSING RIGHT NOW!

424
00:16:04,548 --> 00:16:05,841
FINE, I GET IT.
YOU'RE MAD.

425
00:16:05,924 --> 00:16:09,052
THIS IS WHAT MAD
LOOKS LIKE!

426
00:16:09,136 --> 00:16:10,804
(SIGHS HEAVILY)

427
00:16:10,888 --> 00:16:14,808
BUT UNDERNEATH THE MAD
IS A LOT OF WORRY, FIONA!

428
00:16:14,892 --> 00:16:17,603
YOU'VE ALREADY LOST
ONE SEMESTER!

429
00:16:18,896 --> 00:16:20,647
YOU CAN'T AFFORD
TO LOSE ANOTHER.

430
00:16:20,731 --> 00:16:22,107
BUT I DON'T NEED SCHOOL.

431
00:16:22,191 --> 00:16:23,817
I COULD GET A JOB!

432
00:16:23,901 --> 00:16:24,985
YOU'RE SEVENTEEN.

433
00:16:25,068 --> 00:16:26,987
YOUR JOB IS TO GO
TO SCHOOL.

434
00:16:27,070 --> 00:16:29,656
BUT WHAT IF I HATE IT -
A LOT?!

435
00:16:29,740 --> 00:16:31,116
IF THAT'S TRULY
HOW YOU FEEL,

436
00:16:31,200 --> 00:16:32,159
WE'LL GO BACK TO NEW YORK.

437
00:16:32,242 --> 00:16:33,452
WHAT? NO!

438
00:16:33,535 --> 00:16:34,494
THE ONLY REASON
WHY WE'RE HERE

439
00:16:34,578 --> 00:16:35,829
IS BECAUSE YOU PROMISED

440
00:16:35,913 --> 00:16:37,581
DEGRASSI WOULD BE
GOOD FOR YOU.

441
00:16:37,664 --> 00:16:38,832
(SIGHS)

442
00:16:38,916 --> 00:16:40,250
OKAY, FINE,

443
00:16:41,585 --> 00:16:43,045
I'LL GO TO SCHOOL.

444
00:16:43,128 --> 00:16:45,172
I PROMISE,
NO MORE SKIPPING.

445
00:16:45,255 --> 00:16:46,381
GOOD!

446
00:16:46,465 --> 00:16:48,550
OTHERWISE, YOU'RE ON
THE NEXT PLANE TO LA GUARDIA.

447
00:16:51,803 --> 00:16:53,722
ALLI:
SO, BASICALLY, YOU BLEW IT.

448
00:16:53,805 --> 00:16:56,350
CLARE:
KATIE DIDN'T EVEN READ
MY ARTICLE.

449
00:16:56,433 --> 00:16:58,894
ALLI:
WELL, MAYBE SHE'LL GIVE YOU
A SECOND CHANCE?

450
00:16:58,977 --> 00:16:59,978
(CLARE SIGHS)

451
00:17:03,315 --> 00:17:06,193
THERE SHE IS,
I SHOULD GO TALK TO HER.

452
00:17:06,276 --> 00:17:09,571
NOW LET'S SEE YOUR BEST
"I'M SORRY" FACE.

453
00:17:09,655 --> 00:17:10,572
THAT'LL DO.

454
00:17:10,656 --> 00:17:12,449
NOW, I'LL BE OVER THERE
GETTING MY LATTE ON.

455
00:17:15,327 --> 00:17:17,621
KATIE, CAN WE TALK
FOR A SECOND?

456
00:17:17,704 --> 00:17:19,623
I HAVE SOCCER PRACTICE.

457
00:17:21,834 --> 00:17:23,502
SEE YOU LATER, MARE.

458
00:17:27,172 --> 00:17:29,466
MARISOL, CAN YOU PLEASE
TELL YOUR FRIEND I'M SORRY?

459
00:17:29,550 --> 00:17:31,969
IT'S, UH, GONNA TAKE
MORE THAN THAT.

460
00:17:32,052 --> 00:17:34,721
SEE, KATIE GOES OUT OF HER WAY
TO AVOID DRAMA,

461
00:17:34,805 --> 00:17:37,140
AND YOU...ARE DRAMA.

462
00:17:38,475 --> 00:17:39,768
I AM NOT DRAMA!

463
00:17:46,942 --> 00:17:48,902
♪ These friends of mine ♪

464
00:17:48,986 --> 00:17:51,071
♪ They try, they try ♪

465
00:17:51,154 --> 00:17:53,240
♪ We all struggle,
we all strive ♪

466
00:17:53,323 --> 00:17:55,158
SO WE SHOULD COME UP
WITH SOME BITS

467
00:17:55,242 --> 00:17:57,703
WE CAN USE
OVER AND OVER.

468
00:17:57,786 --> 00:17:59,788
YEAH, LIKE UH...

469
00:17:59,872 --> 00:18:01,456
JOKE OF THE DAY.

470
00:18:01,540 --> 00:18:02,791
YEAH,
OR STUMP THE DORK.

471
00:18:02,875 --> 00:18:04,918
PEOPLE CAN SEND YOU
THEIR TRIVIA QUESTIONS.

472
00:18:05,002 --> 00:18:07,754
EXCUSE ME?
I'M THE DORK?

473
00:18:07,838 --> 00:18:10,424
WE DON'T HAVE
TO CALL IT THAT.

474
00:18:10,507 --> 00:18:12,718
OKAY. UM, ANYWAY,

475
00:18:12,801 --> 00:18:14,052
HOW ABOUT WE DO THIS?

476
00:18:14,136 --> 00:18:15,554
WE CAN DO A QUIZ,
LIKE...

477
00:18:15,637 --> 00:18:17,639
HERE, HAND ME YOUR PEN.

478
00:18:18,932 --> 00:18:20,767
WHAT IS YOUR PROBLEM?

479
00:18:20,851 --> 00:18:21,852
NO PROBLEM.

480
00:18:22,853 --> 00:18:24,771
WAS IT SOMETHING I DID?

481
00:18:24,855 --> 00:18:26,690
I MEAN, EVER SINCE YOU RAN
OUT OF THE BATHROOM...

482
00:18:26,773 --> 00:18:30,027
LOOK, ADAM, IT'S NOT YOU,
IT'S NOT THE BATHROOM.

483
00:18:30,110 --> 00:18:31,778
WE'RE GOOD.

484
00:18:31,862 --> 00:18:32,863
OKAY.

485
00:18:34,615 --> 00:18:37,492
I, UH, JUST HAD
TOO MUCH CAFFEINE.

486
00:18:38,493 --> 00:18:39,786
COOL.

487
00:18:39,870 --> 00:18:43,665
WELL, WE SHOULD PROBABLY
GET BACK TO WORK.

488
00:18:43,749 --> 00:18:45,334
I, UH, HAVE TO...

489
00:18:46,335 --> 00:18:48,170
JUST GIVE ME A MINUTE.

490
00:18:56,220 --> 00:18:58,388
BATHROOM BRAINSTORM,
I HAVE ANOTHER IDEA.

491
00:18:58,472 --> 00:18:59,848
AND IT COULDN'T WAIT?

492
00:18:59,932 --> 00:19:02,226
WELL, I GOTTA GO TOO.

493
00:19:05,229 --> 00:19:07,147
SO ON "JESSE AND GENE,"

494
00:19:08,357 --> 00:19:12,152
THEY USED TO WRITE
NEW LYRICS TO OLD SONGS.

495
00:19:12,236 --> 00:19:13,987
I MEAN,
THEY WERE NO WEIRD AL,

496
00:19:14,071 --> 00:19:15,531
BUT IT WAS PRETTY GOOD.

497
00:19:15,614 --> 00:19:17,699
WHAT-WHAT ARE YOU DOING?

498
00:19:17,783 --> 00:19:19,368
JUST GOING TO THE BATHROOM.

499
00:19:21,954 --> 00:19:24,248
ADAM:
SO THIS ONE TIME,

500
00:19:24,331 --> 00:19:25,832
GENE SANG LIKE
THIS DYING OLD GUY,

501
00:19:25,916 --> 00:19:26,875
AND INSTEAD
OF "CRY ME A RIVER,"

502
00:19:26,959 --> 00:19:28,627
IT WAS "BUY ME A LIVER."

503
00:19:28,710 --> 00:19:29,753
WHAT-WHAT IS THAT?

504
00:19:29,837 --> 00:19:30,796
NOBODY SAID
YOU HAVE TO STARE!

505
00:19:30,879 --> 00:19:31,964
OH! AH!

506
00:19:32,047 --> 00:19:33,131
DUDE! MY SHOES!

507
00:19:33,215 --> 00:19:34,842
I'M SORRY, I'M STILL TRYING
TO FIGURE OUT

508
00:19:34,925 --> 00:19:36,051
HOW TO WORK THIS THING.

509
00:19:36,134 --> 00:19:37,386
OH, GROSS!

510
00:19:37,469 --> 00:19:39,012
OH! THIS- LOOK,
THIS IS TOO MUCH!

511
00:19:39,096 --> 00:19:40,514
ADAM:
DAVE, COME ON.
I'M SORRY!

512
00:19:40,597 --> 00:19:43,809
LOOK, JUST STAY AWAY
FROM ME, OKAY?

513
00:19:43,892 --> 00:19:46,144
(BATHROOM DOOR SLAMS)

514
00:19:48,981 --> 00:19:49,982
(SIGHS HEAVILY)

515
00:19:54,278 --> 00:19:56,029
HEY CHARLIE, IT'S ME.

516
00:19:57,573 --> 00:19:58,574
AGAIN.

517
00:19:59,950 --> 00:20:03,328
I HOPE YOU GOT MY MESSAGES
FROM LAST NIGHT.

518
00:20:03,412 --> 00:20:05,914
(SIGHS)
I HOPE YOU'RE NOT MAD.

519
00:20:07,374 --> 00:20:09,084
THE CAR'S DOWNSTAIRS!

520
00:20:11,420 --> 00:20:13,213
GOTTA GO TO SCHOOL.

521
00:20:13,297 --> 00:20:15,465
BUT PLEASE...
CALL ME BACK.

522
00:20:17,259 --> 00:20:19,344
(PHONE BEEPS)

523
00:20:22,806 --> 00:20:23,974
LARA:
DON'T OBSESS, SHE'LL CALL.

524
00:20:23,974 --> 00:20:25,058
♪ Everything is gonna change ♪

525
00:20:25,058 --> 00:20:26,059
(SIGHS)

526
00:20:26,143 --> 00:20:28,896
♪ Everything is wrong ♪

527
00:20:28,979 --> 00:20:32,191
♪ Wrong people are being loved ♪

528
00:20:32,274 --> 00:20:33,817
♪ wrong ones dying ♪

529
00:20:33,901 --> 00:20:35,152
HEY, IS DAVE ALMOST HERE?

530
00:20:35,235 --> 00:20:37,279
UM... YEAH,
ANY-ANY MINUTE NOW.

531
00:20:38,280 --> 00:20:40,824
I CAN'T WAIT TO HEAR YOU GUYS
TOP YESTERDAY'S SHOW.

532
00:20:40,908 --> 00:20:42,910
FOR SURE,
IT'LL BE SICK.

533
00:20:45,204 --> 00:20:46,205
HEY.

534
00:20:51,210 --> 00:20:53,879
HEY, I'M-I'M STILL REALLY SORRY
ABOUT YESTERDAY.

535
00:20:53,962 --> 00:20:56,465
YEAH,
LET'S JUST DO THE SHOW.

536
00:20:56,548 --> 00:20:58,509
YEAH, WE'RE BOTH MEN.

537
00:20:58,592 --> 00:20:59,885
WHO NEEDS TO TALK,
RIGHT?

538
00:20:59,968 --> 00:21:01,178
MAYBE THAT CAN BE THE TOPIC.

539
00:21:02,304 --> 00:21:04,389
HEY DEGRASSI,
WELCOME TO "MANO A MANO"

540
00:21:04,473 --> 00:21:05,974
WITH DAVE AND ADAM!

541
00:21:06,058 --> 00:21:06,975
LET ME TELL YOU,

542
00:21:07,059 --> 00:21:08,310
IT DOES NOT SMELL GOOD
IN THE BOOTH TODAY,

543
00:21:08,393 --> 00:21:10,312
SO LAY OFF THE BURRITOS
OUT THERE!

544
00:21:10,395 --> 00:21:11,396
(FORCED LAUGH)

545
00:21:11,480 --> 00:21:13,899
WHAT I WANT TO TALK ABOUT TODAY
IS BATHROOM RULES.

546
00:21:13,982 --> 00:21:16,151
NOW, NOT TO GET
ALL POLITICALLY INCORRECT,

547
00:21:16,235 --> 00:21:18,153
BUT SHOULD GIRLS
BE ALLOWED

548
00:21:18,237 --> 00:21:20,572
TO USE THE GUYS' BATHROOM
AT SCHOOL?

549
00:21:20,656 --> 00:21:21,823
SAV:
DAVE, SERIOUSLY, WATCH IT!

550
00:21:21,907 --> 00:21:23,408
DAVE:
BECAUSE HOW I SEE IT IS,
I MEAN...

551
00:21:23,492 --> 00:21:24,409
YOU'RE IN THERE
DOING YOUR THING,

552
00:21:24,493 --> 00:21:25,827
AND ALL OF A SUDDEN

553
00:21:25,911 --> 00:21:27,621
THERE'S A TRANNY
STARING AT YOUR JUNK!

554
00:21:27,704 --> 00:21:29,081
SAV:
DAVE!

555
00:21:29,164 --> 00:21:30,082
WHY IS THIS COOL?

556
00:21:30,165 --> 00:21:32,584
(CUTS TO A SONG)
THAT'S IT, I'M CUTTING YOU OFF.

557
00:21:32,668 --> 00:21:33,669
DAVE:
TEXT ME.

558
00:21:36,588 --> 00:21:38,507
LET ME KNOW
WHAT YOU THINK.

559
00:21:42,553 --> 00:21:43,846
NOT COOL, DAVE.

